<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09067h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09067h">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09067h"> 67(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Chalk Sunday / bachelor baiting / Lent</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Rounding up the Old Bachelors / Shrovetide Pranks</b> The first Sunday in <mark>Lent</mark> brought a new terror to the helpless <mark>bachelor</mark>. It was popularly known as &ldquo;<mark>Chalk Sunday</mark>,&rdquo; and for this reason. Impish lads lay in wait for unmarried men on their way to Mass, and marked a heavy streak of chalk on the back of their best Sunday coats. <small> <a name="II28feb24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#II28feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (28 February 1924) 6/5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
